The evidence with the title 'Labor's Southern Strategy | dollars & sense ' says For example, Boeing moved production of their 787 Dreamliner from union-strong Seattle to non-union, right-to-work South Carolina and then offered an ultimatum to the Seattle Machinists  ... The first time the UFCW tried to organize the plant in 1994 , they thought they could just go through the normal NLRB procedures. 
